    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Implement missing time_source_iq_add function for IQ sample time management\n\n### Summary\nThe `time_source_iq_add` function referenced in timing modules was not implemented in the codebase. When modules attempted to call this function for adding time-stamped IQ samples, the calls would fail or cause undefined behavior.\n\nThis fix implements the missing `time_source_iq_add` function along with related time source IQ management functions in a new time_manager module.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/time_manager/time_source.c`: New implementation of `time_source_iq_add`, `time_source_iq_get`, `time_source_iq_init`, and `time_source_iq_reset` functions\n- `common/utils/time_manager/time_source.h`: Header file with function declarations and documentation\n- `common/utils/CMakeLists.txt`: Added time_manager subdirectory and linked time_manager library to utils\n- `common/utils/time_manager/CMakeLists.txt`: CMake configuration for the new time_manager library\n- `common/utils/time_manager/test_time_source.c`: Test file demonstrating usage of the new functions\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Attempt to compile or link any module that references `time_source_iq_add`\n2. Observe linker errors about undefined reference to `time_source_iq_add`\n3. Alternatively, if forward declarations were used, observe runtime crashes when calling the function\n\nWith this fix, the function now properly performs complex addition of IQ samples while maintaining timing information, returning appropriate error codes for invalid inputs.\n"
}